.TH "NAMED-CHECKCONF" "1" "@RELEASE_DATE@" "9.21.21" "BIND 9"
.SH NAME
named-checkconf \- named configuration file syntax checking tool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.sp
\fBnamed\-checkconf\fP [\fB\-achjklnvz\fP] [\fB\-pe\fP [\fB\-x\fP ]] [\fB\-b\fP]
[\fB\-t\fP directory] {filename}
.SH DESCRIPTION
.sp
\fBnamed\-checkconf\fP checks the syntax, but not the semantics, of a
\fBnamed\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named> configuration file. The file, along with all files included by it, is parsed and checked for syntax
errors. If no file is specified,
\fB@SYSCONFDIR@/named.conf\fP is read by default.
.sp
Note: files that \fBnamed\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named> reads in separate parser contexts, such as
\fBrndc.conf\fP or \fBrndc.key\fP, are not automatically read by
\fBnamed\-checkconf\fP\&.  Configuration errors in these files may cause
\fBnamed\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named> to fail to run, even if \fBnamed\-checkconf\fP was
successful.  However, \fBnamed\-checkconf\fP can be run on these files
explicitly.
.SH OPTIONS
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-a
Don\(aqt check the \fIdnssec\-policy\fP\(aqs DNSSEC key algorithms against
those supported by the crypto provider.  This is useful when checking
a \fInamed.conf\fP intended to be run on another machine with possibly a
different set of supported DNSSEC key algorithms.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-b
This option prints the built\-in server confguration for \fBnamed\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named>\&.
See \fB\-e\fP for more details.
.sp
Note that default settings may change between releases, so this
information is only reliable if \fBnamed\-checkconf\fP and
\fBnamed\fP are from the same release.
.sp
When \fB\-b\fP is in use, the other switches are ignored.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-e
This option prints the effective server configuration that would
result from \fBnamed.conf\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named\:.conf> and its included files, if no errors
were detected, in canonical form.
.sp
The effective configuration is the result of loading a configuration
file and applying it on top of the default settings for \fBnamed\fP\&.
All configurable settings are included.
.sp
Note that default settings may change between releases, so the
effective configuration generated by \fBnamed\-checkconf\fP is only
expected to be correct for the same version of \fBnamed\fP,
built with the same compile\-time options.
.sp
See also the \fB\-b\fP, \fB\-x\fP and \fB\-p\fP options.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-h
This option prints the usage summary and exits.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-j
When loading a zonefile, this option instructs \fBnamed\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named> to read the journal if it exists.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-k
Check the \fIdnssec\-policy\fP\(aqs DNSSEC keys against the key files in
the \fIkey\-directory\fP\&.  This is useful when checking a \fInamed.conf\fP
to ensure a DNSSEC policy matches the existing keys.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-l
This option lists all the configured zones. Each line of output contains the zone
name, class (e.g. IN), view, and type (e.g. primary or secondary).
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-c
This option specifies that only the \(dqcore\(dq configuration should be checked. This suppresses the loading of
plugin modules, and causes all parameters to \fBplugin\fP statements to
be ignored.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-i
This option ignores warnings on deprecated options.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-n
Do not print errors when encountering options that are disabled in
this build. This allows checking of configuration files for other
builds, in which those options are enabled.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-p
This option prints the contents of \fBnamed.conf\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named\:.conf> and all
included files in canonical form, if no errors were detected. See also
the \fB\-x\fP and \fB\-e\fP options.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-t directory
This option instructs \fBnamed\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named> to chroot to \fBdirectory\fP, so that \fBinclude\fP directives in the
configuration file are processed as if run by a similarly chrooted
\fBnamed\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named>\&.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-v
This option prints the version of the \fBnamed\-checkconf\fP program and exits.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-x
When printing the configuration files in canonical form, this option obscures
shared secrets by replacing them with strings of question marks
(\fB?\fP). This allows the contents of \fBnamed.conf\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named\:.conf> and related files
to be shared \- for example, when submitting bug reports \-
without compromising private data. This option cannot be used without
\fB\-p\fP\&.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B \-z
This option performs a test load of all zones of type \fBprimary\fP found in \fBnamed.conf\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named\:.conf>\&.
.UNINDENT
.INDENT 0.0
.TP
.B filename
This indicates the name of the configuration file to be checked. If not specified,
it defaults to \fB@SYSCONFDIR@/named.conf\fP\&.
.UNINDENT
.SH RETURN VALUES
.sp
\fBnamed\-checkconf\fP returns an exit status of 1 if errors were detected
and 0 otherwise.
.SH SEE ALSO
.sp
\fBnamed(8)\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named>, \fBnamed\-checkzone(8)\fP \%<#\:std-iscman-named-checkzone>, BIND 9 Administrator Reference Manual.
.SH Author
Internet Systems Consortium
